1943, where he sponsored the legislation that authorized the New York State Thruway. He went on to serve as a diplomat at posts in Greece, the United Kingdom, Burma, and Ghana. He also published a biography of King Mongkut of Siam in 1961 and genealogical works on the Low and Pierrepont family lines.","number":2},{"header":"He compiled the Pierrepont genealogy","body":"In 1962, Abbot Low Moffat published The Pierreponts, 1802-1962, tracing the American forebears and descendants of Hezekiah Beers Pierpont and Anna Maria Constable. The Pierrepont family is central to the Hooker tree: Rev. James Pierpont, great-grandson of Mary Hooker Pierpont, co-founded Yale in 1701. Moffat's Pierrepont genealogy — compiled by a Hooker descendant — is a primary research source for this project.","number":3}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Ambassador Abbot Low Moffat","first_name":"Abbot","last_name":"Moffat","middle_name":"Low","title":"Ambassador","married_names":[],"photo_url":"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcR5tg4syKJuBQ-DBgzaH01FlLpuvzUj8i0XktqF1-j79_MRsEuEq9BY9QJ7L7KvxeAb1wHj6Q&s"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"abbot-moffat-1901"},"neighborhood":{"focus":{"id":"HD1641","slug":"abbot-moffat-1901","n":"Ambassador Abbot Low Moffat","by":1901,"dy":1996,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":10},"spouses":[{"order":1,"spouse":{"id":"I00176","slug":"marion-adams-1905","n":"Marion D. Adams Moffat","by":1905,"dy":1994,"sx":"f","hd":false,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":null},"year":1926,"children":[{"id":"HD3136","slug":"jane-kerin-moffat-1931","n":"Doctor Jane-Kerin Moffat","by":1931,"dy":2021,"sx":"f","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":11},{"id":"HD3137","slug":"burnham-moffat","n":"Burnham Moffat","by":null,"dy":null,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":11},{"id":"HD3138","slug":"nancy-liflan